<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4757/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Riddle</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-22"><hi rend="italic">February 22,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Russian Red Cross is carrying on relief measures and has furnished
                            3,000,000 roubles in last six months, but would nevertheless be grateful
                            for any outside aid.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Riddle.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>